      "rationale": "Three-mesh GCI study yields GCI = 4.1% on predicted MIH at OP3, exceeding the 2% threshold. Temporal convergence is demonstrated. Spatial discretization error remains a gap at MRL 5 requirements. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions match COU operating envelope within ±5% on all boundary condition parameters; fluid temperature, hematocrit, and anticoagulant protocol documented.",
      "rationale": "Bench hemolysis measurements were conducted at 37°C with 30% hematocrit bovine blood. Flow rate control is within ±3%. However, anticoagulant protocol (heparin concentration) is reported as a range rather than a fixed value, introducing unquantified variability. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
