      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs map directly to clinical decision QoIs (absolute MIH); no surrogate QoIs used without demonstrated correlation.",
      "rationale": "Primary validation QoI is MIH, which directly maps to the clinical decision QoI. Pump head is used as a secondary QoI. The hemolysis power law exponent calibration relies on literature data rather than device-specific measurements, introducing model form uncertainty not fully captured. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on identical device geometry and blood analogue under COU flow-speed envelope; no geometric or fluid substitutions without demonstrated equivalence.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic pump geometry, which matches the COU geometry. However, the PIV boundary condition dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-15) was acquired under the prior model configuration and has not been re-evaluated against the January 2026 model revision. The relevance of validation activities to the current model build is therefore reduced. Achieved level 2."
    },
