      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison of at least two closure models against validation data; hemolysis power law constants sourced from device-specific calibration.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model is used. Comparison with realizable k-ε was performed on a single operating point only. Hemolysis power law constants (C, α, β) are taken from Giersiepen et al. (1990) without device-specific recalibration. Model form uncertainty is the dominant epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters sourced from measurements post-dating the current model revision; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed on inputs with documented probability distributions.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed with 500 samples. Input distributions for viscosity and density are well-characterized. Critically, the inlet velocity profile boundary conditions are derived from the PIV dataset with dataVintage 2025-10-15, which predates the model revision of 2026-01-20. The revised near-wall treatment alters the sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to inlet turbulence intensity, meaning the pre-revision PIV-derived inputs may not be appropriate for the current model build. Re-validation of inputs against the revised model is planned for Q2 2026 but has not been completed. Achieved level 2.",
      "staleInputNote": "PIV dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-15) predates modelRevisionDate (2026-01-20); input re-validation is planned but not complete."
